docs.lead_paragraph: Considerable irregularity marked trading in bonds yesterday on the Stock Exchange, but prices finished generally steady. Domestic corporation issues averaged slightly higher as leading foreign loans lost ground. Long-term United States Government obligations ended 4-32 point higher to 3-32 lower. The turnover declined to $15,337,500, the smallest in several days.

docs.snippet: The dollar was strong in terms of the French franc last week. From a low of 62.24 cents on Monday, the dollar climbed to 63.47 cents on Friday, highest in last two weeks. There was a slight decline from this point to 62.99 on Saturday, but withal...
docs.lead_paragraph: The dollar was strong in terms of the French franc last week. From a low of 62.24 cents on Monday, the dollar climbed to 63.47 cents on Friday, highest in last two weeks. There was a slight decline from this point to 62.99 on Saturday, but withal there was a net gain of 0.21 cent over the previous week. Range a year ago, 100.39@100.14.

docs.lead_paragraph: Leaders of women's organizations, experts on international law and others paid tribute last night to Doris Stevens, chairman of the Inter-American Commission of Women, at a testimonial dinner at the Park Lane, honoring her success in obtaining international legislation for women at the recently concluded seventh Pan-American Conference in Montevideo.
